                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.51632 National City Bank/2: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-02-28T12:00:00-03:00"
                            >February 28, 1930—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received February 28—11:20
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5. Department’s telegram No. 6, February 27, 7 p.m. Facts reported through the
                    Department by bank substantially correct and matter has been in conference
                    between local branch authorities and Embassy for some time.</p>
                <p>Will use influence with Foreign Office to obtain postponement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
